  <datafield tag="545" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Episcopal priest, member of the executive committee of the Metropolitan Detroit Citizens Development Authority, civic organization established with the goals of improving the economic, social, educational, cultural and general welfare of the people of the city of Detroit, Michigan; also coordinator of the assistant superintendant and ombudsman for the Ann Arbor Public Schools.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Executive committee minutes, board reports, and other materials relating to his activities with the Metropolitan Detroit Citizens Development Authority and to the Mayor's Youth Opportunity Council; files relating to his work as an ombudsman in the Ann Arbor public school system and as a member of the board of Avalon Housing in Ann Arbor; sermons and other materials relating to his responsibilities as an Episcopal priest within the Diocese of Michigan. The collection offers perspective into social, economic, and racial issues in both Ann Arbor and Detroit during the 1960's, 70's, and 80's.</subfield>
  </datafield>
